data.text/markdown:
Linear Regression Example

... or can I just ask AI to "analyze the data"?

Imagine that you've asked a chatbot how to run linear regression on four sets of data.

Anscombe's Quartet

Let's see what happens.

data.text/markdown:
Incredible! (in the most literal sense) we're getting identical ||(R^2||) and identical lines for 4 different sets of data.

But let's plot it...
Well, that's not great.

Example 2: Auto MPG

Relationship between engine horsepower and fuel efficiency (MPG).

data.text/markdown:
||(R^2||) = 0.606 and Slope = -0.158

Great! Negatively correlated, as expected, with reasonably high explainability. But there's a problem when we look at the graph.

The Problem:

||(R^2||) = 0.606 looks decent, but:
  • The plots shows a clear nonlinearity.
  • The linear model is systematically wrong. It underestimates at extremes and overestimates in middle.
Just asking an LLM for a linear regression, you might not catch this unless you tell it to check.
